<p>Suppose we do a probability experiment with a mass production of light bulbs. We take a sample size of 120. Define two chance variables: <em>X</em> is the number of bulbs that are defective, and <em>Y</em> is the burn time per bulb. Which random variable in this probability experiment is a continuous variable?</p>
</p>]]></text>
